Organize-m Release Notes v0.8.4
-------------------------------
- Bug fix: Make command-line-operation more reliable
- Bug fix: find() and show() commands don't return sorted items
- Bug fix: regex comparisons handle exception on illegal matching pattern, return message to user
- Docs: Modified README to be HTML format
- Docs: Added wiki documentation for manual editing and command-line interface cookbook and reference
- Feature: rebuild_grouped now adds group labels as YAML comments to mark each group in the data file
- Feature: Added shebang to orgm.py to support running on Mac and *nix without 'python orgm.py' before commands
- Feature: find() now returns 'no items found' message if no items found instead of nothing
- Code quality: Refactored code